article.headline: Colorado 98, Buffalo 47
article.story:
BOULDER, Colo. (AP) -- Kate Fagan led all scorers with 24 points
as No. 13 Colorado beat Buffalo 98-47 Saturday night.

Colorado(11-1) set a new school record with 16 3-pointers.

Four other Colorado players scored in double figures. Tera
Bjorklund had 16 points, Amber Metoyer and Emily Waner had 12
points each and Leslie Howard added 11.

Brook Meunier led the way for the Buffalo Bulls (1-7) with 13
points, all in the second half, while Jessica Kochendorfer had nine
points and 11 rebounds.

Colorado opened the game with a 21-4 lead and Buffalo was never
closer than 17, trailing Colorado 42-14 at the half.

The Bulls shot 35 percent from the field, and 16 percent from
beyond the arc. Colorado was 49 percent from the floor and 43
percent from 3-point range.
